! Overview of Mnemonic Techniques
Memory techniques leverage **visualization**, **association**, and **structure** to encode abstract information (like lists or numbers) into memorable mental images.

!! 1. Peg Method vs. Memory Palace
| !Method | !Mechanism | !Best For |
|''Peg Method'' |Associates items with a pre-memorized list of "pegs" (e.g., 1=Bun, 2=Shoe). |Short to medium ordered lists. |
|''Memory Palace'' |Places mental images in specific physical locations (Loci) within a familiar building. |Long sequences and complex information. |

* **Key Difference:** The Peg Method uses a fixed verbal list as an anchor, while the Memory Palace uses spatial navigation.

